<!-- ABOUT -->
<section id="about" data-reveal>
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-label">About</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">About The Mind&rsquo;s Gambit</h2>
    <div class="section-divider"></div>
    <div class="about-purpose" style="max-width:820px;margin:0 auto 2.4rem"><h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',Georgia,serif;color:#e8e0d0;font-size:1.35rem;margin:0 0 0.7rem">What this site is for</h3><p style="color:rgba(232,224,208,0.78);font-size:1.02rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1rem">The Mind&rsquo;s Gambit is two things at once: a free chess school and a long-form writing project about the human mind under pressure. The school gives beginners, returning adults, parents, and young competitors a complete, structured path &mdash; tactics from scratch, pawn structures, an engine-verified opening repertoire, written lessons, training tools, and a library of master games &mdash; with no ads, no accounts, and no paywall. The writing &mdash; a published book, a documentary series, and The Daily Gambit newspaper &mdash; examines what chess reveals about genius, obsession, and mental health.</p><p style="color:rgba(232,224,208,0.78);font-size:1.02rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1rem">Our mission is simple: chess education of professional quality, free to anyone with a browser &mdash; and an honest accounting of the game&rsquo;s human cost, told with care.</p></div><h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',Georgia,serif;color:#e8e0d0;font-size:1.35rem;margin:0 0 0.7rem">Who&rsquo;s behind it</h3><div class="about-content">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>I&rsquo;m a chess player and a lifelong student of the game. I bring a distinctive perspective to the world of chess&mdash;one shaped not by grandmaster ambitions but by a career spent in the most consequential arenas of human struggle. A graduate of Illinois State University with a degree in Sociology, I have devoted my professional life to child protection and mental health&mdash;fields that have given me a profound understanding of how individuals navigate systemic pressure, institutional failure, and the quiet crises that unfold far from public view.</p>
        <p>My encounter with chess began during graduate studies in International Affairs at The New School in Manhattan, where afternoons spent at the stone chess tables of Stuyvesant Town became an unexpected counterweight to the global complexities of the classroom. What started as a neighborhood pastime grew into a lifelong fascination with the game's social dimensions&mdash;its hierarchies, its rituals, its capacity to both heal and harm.</p>
        <p>I later deepened my engagement with the chess community through the Pittsburgh Chess League and the University of Pittsburgh Chess Club&mdash;experiences that sharpened the questions at the heart of my work: Who benefits from chess, and who is left behind? What happens to the mind under sustained competitive pressure? And what obligations do the institutions of chess owe to the people who entrust their development to the game?</p>
        <p>I am the author of <em>The Mind's Gambit: Chess, Madness, and the Battle for the Mind</em>, now available in ebook, paperback, hardcover, and audiobook. If the book speaks to you, an honest review would be deeply appreciated.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-sidebar">
        <div class="about-photo">
          <img src="/images/Me.JPG" alt="Mourad Bouajaja, author of The Mind's Gambit" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="label">Background</div>
          <div class="value">Child Protection &amp; Mental Health</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="label">Education</div>
          <div class="value">Illinois State (Sociology) &middot; The New School (Int'l Affairs)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="label">Chess Community</div>
          <div class="value">Pittsburgh Chess League &middot; University of Pittsburgh Chess Club</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="label">Published 2026</div>
          <div class="value"><em>The Mind's Gambit</em> &mdash; A Book in Ten Chapters</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  <div class="about-trust" style="max-width:820px;margin:2.6rem auto 0"><h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',Georgia,serif;color:#e8e0d0;font-size:1.35rem;margin:0 0 0.7rem">Transparency &amp; trust</h3><p style="color:rgba(232,224,208,0.78);font-size:1.02rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1rem">The Mind&rsquo;s Gambit is published by <strong>MYB Studio LLC</strong>, an independent studio operating out of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. Everything here is heavily researched before it is published: opening lines are verified move by move against the Stockfish engine, historical claims are checked against primary sources and archives, and our film restorations are made from original public-domain prints. When we recommend a book or piece of equipment, the recommendation comes first and the affiliate link second &mdash; and we disclose it plainly on the page. If we get something wrong, <a href="/#contact" style="color:#c9a84c">write to us</a> and we will correct it.</p><p style="color:rgba(232,224,208,0.6);font-size:.92rem;line-height:1.8;margin:1.1rem 0 0"><strong style="color:rgba(232,224,208,0.85)">MYB Studio LLC</strong><br/>6375 Penn Ave Suite B #1200 &middot; Pittsburgh, PA 15206<br/>Tel: <a href="tel:+14124558824" style="color:#c9a84c;text-decoration:none">(412) 455-8824</a> &middot; Fax: (412) 332-8171 &middot; <a href="mailto:hello@mybouajaja.com" style="color:#c9a84c;text-decoration:none">hello@mybouajaja.com</a></p></div></div>
</section>

